	<body>
		<h1>My personal web site</h1>
		<img width="80" height="80" src="./avatar.png" alt="Avatar" />
		<h3>Greetings</h3>
		<p><strong> Made by: </strong> Altamoid <br /></p>
		<p>
			This is just what I got at the beginning. People around are just like
			"This person doesn't know nothing" but in the sense that I'm a moron.
			Anyway I do my best to learn the things that make this world
		</p>
		<hr />
		<p><i>2026-01-15:</i> <strong> Unraveling the confusion </strong></p>
		These are the things that introduce me into a mix of frustration, fear and
		surprise today:
		<ul>
			<li>
				People saying stuff that I don't know what they mean and they get
				confused because they thought that I already know it
			</li>
			<li>I got punished by not eating all day long</li>
			<li>
				The punishment that my sister put me because I was polite with an old
				man
			</li>
			<li>Why I would use twitter (X)?</li>
			<li>
				People reproach me because I said "dumb" to a dumb and I can't protest
				because the same people call me "dumb"
			</li>
			<li>
				I don't know what they see as special about the movie "K-pop demon
				hunters"
			</li>
			<li>
				When I get reward, I have the feeling that there was something else
				doing the hard work for me and I was just doing the easiest part. So I
				think that I'm a fraud
			</li>
			<li>I don't know where to start by using my phone</li>
		</ul>
		So I have to find the ways that I can solve that sort of problems
		<hr />
		<p><i>2026-01-26:</i> <strong> Some revelation </strong></p>
		<p>
			I found out that everything that I used to think was a perception of not
			doing anything in the life. It is like we as human beings we must do stuff
			around that go like creating other stuff in music, taking care of the ones
			you love.
		</p>
		<p>
			If I have to think about "loving someone", I ought to learn other
			spiritual concept that makes us believe that something or someone is very
			good for us. I specifically go to the "spiritual" domain instead of
			psychological, mental or even physiological, because all of them study the
			reaction of the romanticism in that thing; being in love with someone and
			loving someone are two different things that may seem the same, but
			they're different in practice.
		</p>
		<p>
			While I was writing this, I was asking myself: Is this site written
			properly? Or people would laugh at the way I expose my ideas on the
			Internet? After all, I do this for the same reason people use social
			media: Watching what people do with their time
		</p>
		<hr />
		<p><i>2026-01-31:</i> <strong> Being irresponsible </strong></p>
		<p>
			When I decided to check my discord account again, I was tempted by my
			contacts to write something that would seem interesting. I wrote about the
			"Hardest question in programming" and then I was determined to write
			something else in this diary that I will post on the Internet as an
			alternative communication method on social media.
		</p>
		<p>
			There came an inspiration to do something that I really liked when I was a
			child, maybe it was the previous version of what we call "gachas", but for
			me they were (and still are) funnier than them; I am referring to
			"walfas". After thinking about it, I was tempted to create the thing I
			call "Altamoid" (Don't ask me how I thought about the name, because I
			actually don't know the meaning of it):
		</p>
		<div>
			<img src="./salidas/altamoid.png" alt="Altamoid" />
		</div>
		<div>
			Here we got some Characteristics:
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>What he likes: </strong>Coffee, rice, computers and some books
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>What he hates: </strong>Arts, expensive things and caprice
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>What he does: </strong>Working for a mad girl to make his
					father happy
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Characteristics: </strong>A little bit clumsy, used to have
					cheap things, obsessive with freedom, willing to experiment stuff
				</li>
				<li><strong>Anything else? </strong>Nothing but just a guy</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<hr />
		<p><i>2026-02-01:</i> <strong> Another intention </strong></p>
		<p>
			I used once "character.ia", and personally I have to think that it was a
			good way to know about series and franchises, but it is not a good way to
			knwo about the characters or to be with them as how they were created. So
			now I came up with an idea: I want to create my own chat that imitates a
			character. The reason for that is when I used the Alastor character, I did
			some strange comments like saying that I would work for the hotel he owns;
			which is pretty odd if you know about the Hazbin Hotel franchise.
		</p>
		<p>
			Another weird thing I did by testing the site is using the chats that
			simulates a talk with the king Terry A. Davis and he didn't come out with
			delirious and racist epithets twisted with his amazing programming skills.
			The chat appologized for not saying something like that instead, which
			disappointed me and I decided to create something that could express
			beyond its limits but without being intentionally aggressive.
		</p>
		<p>
			I tried also with Bakugo, Twilight, Zenku and Oh Yul as far as I remember,
			it was interesing to know how many situations could suscitate after
			writting the most bizarre comments to them. But when I knew how were the
			characters, I got frustrated after applying that matter in "character.ia".
			By the way,
			<a href="https://youtu.be/B5YokNW7tIs?si=xxoPzG4cgmfRMDLf">this</a> is one
			of my favorite clips of Terry :).
		</p>
		<hr />
		<p><i>2026-02-28:</i> <strong> Overwhelm </strong></p>
		<p>
			Now that I'm back in the studio again, I come across a topic that just
			makes me nervous: The issue of revising concepts that I hated at first
			because they represented a means for various groups to be greedy, to be
			companies that try to make computers advance but that the machinery is
			only available to other groups. Today I met Linus Torvalds commenting
			several years ago that while the FSF has good intentions, the truth is
			that when it comes to supporting the intentions that Linus had for people
			who used not only his kernel, but other programs with the intention of
			checking how many bugs he might have for later use by end users. If you
			want to know when did he say that,
			<a href="https://youtu.be/PaKIZ7gJlRU?si=WMcWoNlLqRWj4nxT">here it is</a>.
		</p>
		<p>
			I also found that my degree project was already done, what happened was
			that I didn't know that there was someone who had already done it.
			However, when I check it with the teacher I have, it seems that it is an
			idea that could work out well for personal development and also as a
			product for the degree.
		</p>
		<p>
			With all these tangling thoughts, I remember in a relief instant
			<a href=" https://youtu.be/hpnjW0UHtX8?si=_KzdHxJwSJrVO7n5 ">
				this song
			</a>
			from a group I discovered thanks to a friend of mine.
		</p>
		<p>
			<i>
				&#x266B;<br />
				I feel I'm breaking down,<br />
				Man I'm just not myself.<br />
				I feel I'm breaking down,<br />
				Damn, I feel so stressed out!<br />
				&#x266B;<br />
			</i>
		</p>
